'''Jerome Osei Opoku''' (born 14 October 1998) is a professional [[association football|footballer]]. He plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]]. Born in England, he plays for the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

Opoku grew up admiring [[Gareth Bale]] and initially aspired to become a top-class winger. However, during his U-15 years, his coach [[Mark Pembridge]] shifted him to left-back. Around the same time, a sudden growth spurt prompted another change — this time to centre-back — a position he would go on to play for most of his senior career.

As captain of Fulham’s U-16 team, Opoku led the side to victory in the 2014 Premier League International Cup, defeating a highly-rated Chelsea squad in the final.{{citation needed|date=January 2026}}

== Club career ==
He captained the Fulham U23s at the end of the 2018–19 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fulhamfc.com/player-profiles/jerome-opoku|title=JEROME OPOKU FULHAM PROFILE|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>

On 2 September 2019, Opoku was sent on loan to League One side [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] in order to gain first team experience.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49553968|title=ACCRINGTON SIGN JEROME ON LOAN|last=|first=|work=BBC Sport |date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He made his Accrington debut against Bristol Rovers on 7 September 2019 in an eventual 3–3 draw. After a 3–1 defeat to Sunderland, in an interview he claimed he would play anywhere the coach put him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/17907223.fulham-loanee-jerome-opoku-ready-play-anywhere-accrington/|title=JEROME OPOKU READY TO PLAY ANYWHERE|last=|first=|newspaper=Lancashire Telegraph |date=17 September 2019|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>

On 25 September 2020, Opoku joined [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] on loan until January.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pafc.co.uk/news/2020/september/opoku-on-loan/|title=On-Loan Opoku|publisher=[[Plymouth Argyle F.C.]]|date=25 September 2020|access-date=25 September 2020}}</ref>

On 30 July 2021, Opoku was loaned out again, this time to [[Danish Superliga]] club [[Vejle Boldklub]], for the entire 2021–22 season.<ref>[https://vejle-boldklub.dk/vejle-boldklub-lejer-talentfuld-forsvarsspiller-i-fulham-f-c/ Vejle Boldklub lejer talentfuld forsvarsspiller i Fulham F.C.] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211202013536/https://vejle-boldklub.dk/vejle-boldklub-lejer-talentfuld-forsvarsspiller-i-fulham-f-c/ |date=2 December 2021 }}, vejle-boldklub.dk, 30 July 2021</ref>

On 24 June 2022, Opoku joined Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]] side [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]] on a free transfer, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=OficialFCArouca|number=1540349103732916224|title=Bem-vindo a familia, Jerome|date=24 June 2022|access-date=27 June 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=24 June 2022 |title=Jerome Opoku assina com o Arouca por três épocas |trans-title=Jerome Opoku signs with Arouca for three seasons |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/arouca/detalhe/jeromeopoku-assina-com-o-arouca-por-tres-epocas |access-date= |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 14 September 2023, Opoku signed a one-year contract extension with Arouca, until 2026,<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 September 2023 |title=Jerome Opoku renova com o Arouca e sai por empréstimo para o Basaksehir |trans-title=Jerome Opoku renews with Arouca and leaves on loan to Basaksehir |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/arouca/detalhe/noticia-record-jerome-opoku-renova-com-o-arouca-e-sai-por-emprestimo-para-o-basaksehir |access-date= |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref> and was immediately sent on a season-long loan to [[Süper Lig]] side [[İstanbul Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-14 |title=HOŞ GELDİN JEROME OPOKU |trans-title=Welcome Jerome Opoku |url=https://ibfk.com.tr/haberler/hos-geldin-jerome-opoku |access-date= |website= |publisher=İstanbul Başakşehir FK |language=tr}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in England, Opoku is of Ghanaian descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footballghana.com/ghanaian-defender-jerome-opoku-in-line-for-contract-extension-at-fulham|title=Ghanaian defender Jerome Opoku in line for contract extension at Fulham|website=Footballghana}}</ref> On 18 October 2023, he debuted for the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] in a friendly loss to the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States national team]].<ref>{{Cite web | title=Jerome Opoku makes Ghana debut against USA - Get Sports Gh | url=https://getsportsgh.com/2023/10/18/jerome-opoku-makes-ghana-debut-against-usa/ | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231218230532/https://getsportsgh.com/2023/10/18/jerome-opoku-makes-ghana-debut-against-usa/ | access-date=2025-04-28 | archive-date=2023-12-18}}</ref>

